<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial laundry repair, what SoCal operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the difference between commercial laundry repair and laundry service?</h3>
        <p>We repair the machines, washers and dryers that stop working. Laundry service companies pick up dirty laundry and return it clean. We fix equipment on-site at your building or laundromat. We don't pick up or clean laundry.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover for commercial laundry repair?</h3>
        <p>Same-day across <strong>Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties</strong>, Koreatown, Hollywood, Long Beach LA-side; Anaheim, Garden Grove, Costa Mesa OC; Thousand Oaks and Oxnard Ventura; Rancho Cucamonga, Riverside, Ontario IE. Eight service territories total. BHGS #A49573.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How quickly can you repair commercial laundry equipment?</h3>
        <p>Same day for most calls across all five SoCal counties. Call {phone} before noon and we typically dispatch that day. For apartment buildings with tenant complaints active, we route as priority. Describe all machines needing service when you call so we bring parts for multiple repairs in one visit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you service multiple washers and dryers on the same visit?</h3>
        <p>Yes. For laundromats and apartment buildings, we prioritize servicing all affected units on the same trip. Describe every machine and symptom when you call, this lets us bring appropriate parts and minimize return visits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair coin-operated washers and dryers?</h3>
        <p>Yes, the mechanical and electrical systems. For coin acceptor and card reader electronics specifically, we assess on-site and advise whether it requires the payment system vendor. Most coin-op failures are the machine, not the payment system.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you service all commercial laundry brands?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Speed Queen, Dexter, Huebsch, Maytag Commercial, Continental Girbau, UniMac, Wascomat, Electrolux Professional, Milnor. Speed Queen parts on the van, the dominant brand in SoCal multi-family laundry rooms across all five counties.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you offer maintenance contracts for laundromats and apartment buildings?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Scheduled maintenance visits, priority dispatch, and multi-machine service programs. For property management companies with multiple buildings, we build service plans around your portfolio. Call to discuss your machine inventory and service needs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

